{
  "texts": [
    "The variational mean q(c ik |x i; α) is used as the inferred cell state proportions.",
    "For BayesPrism, we followed the tutorial on the BayesPrism website: https://www.bayesprism.org/pages/tutorial_deconvolution.",
    "We subsetted the common protein-coding genes between the scRNA-seq and ST data with highly variable gene selection by default.",
    "We ran the BayesPrism Gibbs sampler 'run.prism' with four cores and extracted the updated cell type fractions θ n for deconvolution.",
    "For Cell2location, we followed the tutorial on the Cell2location website: https://cell2location.readthedocs.io/en/latest/notebooks/ cell2location_tutorial.html."
  ]
}